# ==============================================================================
# Takumi Docker Build Context Ignore Rules
#
# [Why] To reduce build time and prevent sensitive data leakage.
# [What] Excludes secrets, heavy assets, logs, and local environment configs.
# ==============================================================================

# --- 1. Security & Secrets (CRITICAL) ---
# [Why] To ensure secrets are NEVER baked into the image layers.
.env
.env.keys
.env.*.local

# --- 2. Heavy Data & Artifacts ---
# [Why] To speed up the "Sending build context to Docker daemon" phase.
# [What] Exclude directories that are mounted at runtime or downloaded by the installer.
app/ComfyUI/
cache/
external/
logs/
storage/
takumi_train_data/

# Large binary files (Safety net)
*.safetensors
*.ckpt
*.pth
*.bin
*.onnx
*.engine

# --- 3. Version Control & CI ---
.git
.gitignore
.dockerignore
.github/
Dockerfile
Makefile
README.md
PRIVACY.md

# --- 4. Logs & Artifacts ---
*.log
logs/
*.jsonl
.install_history

# --- 5. System & IDE ---
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- 6. Language Runtime Junk ---
# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/

# Node.js
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log